FBIS3-15060 "drsov041_a_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Agent Worked for Artillery Firm LD0203115894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0941 GMT 2 Mar 94 LD0203115894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, 2 Mar (ITAR-TASS) -- The Russian citizen recruited by British special services, who was arrested on 15 January this year, was a leading employee of the SMM (Special Engineering and Metallurgy) joint-stock company, set up on the basis of enterprises belonging to the former USSR Ministry of Defense Industry. SMM worked on state programs in the sphere of armor and artillery systems. This is disclosed in the Wednesday edition of the newspaper `Segodnya', which quotes Aleksandr Mikhaylov, head of the public relations centre of the Federal Counterintelligence Service. In its article on the detained agent, the newspaper says that the level of this post could illustrate the fact that he had the possibility of direct access to representatives of the legal British intelligence mission, which used the embassy as "cover." The arrested person is accused of passing on top secret information to a foreign special service. The information concerned the latest armaments systems and Russia's overall defense potential. On 25 February he was charged under Article 64, Sub-Section "A" (treason ... [passage indistinct]
